<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd22c0ec4-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s37"><num value="37">§ 37.</num><heading> Violations; punishment</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whoever knowingly commits, instigates, or assists in any act forbidden by <ref href="/us/usc/t47/s34">section 34 of this title</ref> shall be guilty of a misdemeanor and shall be fined not more than $5,000, or imprisoned for not more than one year, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd22c0ec5-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5">(<ref href="/us/act/1921-05-27/ch12/s4">May 27, 1921, ch. 12, § 4</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/8">42 Stat. 8</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd22c0ec6-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idd22c0ec7-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idd22c0ec8-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Submarine Cable Act which comprises this chapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
